                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-8"/>
                    <note type="description">In hagiography: Miles was a Bishop of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/415">Susa</placeName>. He was born near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/875">Tehran</placeName> and converted from Zoroastrianism. He went on a long pilgrimage and opposed the manner of leadership of Catholicos <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/669">Papa</persName>. He was imprisoned with his son Narsai and beaten by the governor Hormizd. The priest <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1544">Aboursam</persName> and the deacon Sinai died with him.</note>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib8-7">male</sex>
